The paper deals with the complexity of comparing integers and rationals represented in a specific notation, which falls under the scope of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of number theory concepts and conjectures suggests a possible fit in information theory (cs.IT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The application of the results to parsing also suggests a possible fit in systems and control (cs.SY).
